---
import PageLayout from "../layouts/PageLayout.astro";
---

<PageLayout
    title="About - OffroadPakistan"
    description="About the OffroadPakistan.com Heritage Archive restoration project and the 4x4 Offroaders Club Karachi"
>
    <!-- Page Header -->
    <header class="mb-8">
        <h1 class="text-sm md:text-base font-bold text-gray-600 mb-2">
            About OffroadPakistan.com
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xs md:text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Heritage archive restoration documenting decades of Pakistani
            adventure
        </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Heritage Story -->
    <section class="mb-8">
        <h2
            class="text-sm md:text-base font-bold text-teal-600 mb-3 border-b border-dotted border-gray-400"
        >
            The Original Site Legacy
        </h2>

        <div class="text-xs md:text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
            <p>
                The original OffroadPakistan.com was founded by Khalid and Abid
                Omar, documenting the adventures of the 4x4 Offroaders Club
                Karachi as they explored Pakistan's most remote and challenging
                terrains. From 2003 to 2008, this website served as the digital
                chronicle of Pakistani off-road enthusiasm.
            </p>

            <p>
                Club members ventured forth where few had gone before - across
                the Thar Desert, through the northern valleys of
                Gilgit-Baltistan, up to K2 Base Camp, and into the cultural
                heartlands of Chitral and the Kalash valleys. Each expedition
                was meticulously documented with photographs and detailed trip
                reports.
            </p>

            <p>
                The website featured a distinctive early 2000s design with a
                fixed 780px layout, heritage color scheme of teals and browns,
                and careful attention to presenting adventure photography with
                the characteristic bordered image style of that era.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Restoration Project -->
    <section class="mb-8">
        <h2
            class="text-sm md:text-base font-bold text-teal-600 mb-3 border-b border-dotted border-gray-400"
        >
            Heritage Archive Restoration
        </h2>

        <div class="text-xs md:text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
            <p>
                This restored site represents a careful preservation effort to
                bring the original OffroadPakistan.com content into the modern
                web era. The original site unfortunately crashed and was lost,
                but the content has been meticulously extracted and restored.
            </p>

            <p>
                <strong>What's been preserved:</strong>
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 space-y-1">
                <li>31 picture galleries with over 1,600 photographs</li>
                <li>Detailed trip reports and adventure stories</li>
                <li>Nearly 2,000 historical comments from the community</li>
                <li>Original heritage design elements and color scheme</li>
                <li>Content organization and navigation structure</li>
            </ul>

            <p>
                <strong>Modern improvements:</strong>
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 space-y-1">
                <li>Fully responsive design for mobile and desktop</li>
                <li>Improved typography and readability</li>
                <li>Fast loading with modern web technologies</li>
                <li>Search engine optimization</li>
                <li>Accessibility enhancements</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Technical Details -->
    <section class="mb-8">
        <h2
            class="text-sm md:text-base font-bold text-teal-600 mb-3 border-b border-dotted border-gray-400"
        >
            Technical Implementation
        </h2>

        <div class="text-xs md:text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
            <p>
                The restored site is built with modern static site generation
                using Astro.js v5 and Tailwind CSS v4, deployed via GitHub
                Pages. All content is stored in Markdown format with frontmatter
                metadata, preserving the original structure while enabling
                modern web practices.
            </p>

            <p>
                The design philosophy balances heritage preservation with modern
                usability - honoring the original's distinctive character while
                ensuring accessibility across all devices and screen sizes.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Community -->
    <section class="mb-8">
        <h2
            class="text-sm md:text-base font-bold text-teal-600 mb-3 border-b border-dotted border-gray-400"
        >
            The 4x4 Offroaders Club Karachi
        </h2>

        <div class="text-xs md:text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
            <p>
                The club members were pioneers of Pakistani adventure travel,
                exploring regions that were largely undocumented in the early
                2000s. Their expeditions opened up new routes and showcased
                Pakistan's incredible natural beauty to a wider audience.
            </p>

            <p>
                As the original site noted: "Our members are a bit shy of the
                keyboard, being more used to Jeeps than computers" - but their
                passion for exploration and documentation created an invaluable
                archive of Pakistani adventure heritage.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Heritage Note -->
    <div
        class="mt-8 p-4 md:p-6 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 text-xs md:text-sm"
    >
        <h3 class="font-bold text-teal-600 mb-3">Preservation Notice</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
            This heritage archive represents an important piece of Pakistani
            adventure travel history. All original content is preserved exactly
            as published, including historical comments and community
            interactions from 2003-2008.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong>Original Site Credits:</strong> Khalid and Abid Omar, 4x4 Offroaders
            Club Karachi<br />
            <strong>Heritage Restoration:</strong> 2024 Archive Project<br />
            <strong>Technical Implementation:</strong> Astro.js with GitHub Pages
            deployment
        </p>
    </div>
</PageLayout>
